{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 2D Heat Equation on a Square with h- and p-Refinement Study\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook solves the 2D heat equation on a square domain \\([0, 1] \\times [0, 1]\\) and performs an h- and p-refinement study to compare the maximum temperature \\( u_{\\text{max}} \\) at \\( t = 0.15 \\) with the analytical solution. The problem is:\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "\\frac{\\partial u}{\\partial t} &= \\kappa \\Delta u, \\quad (x, y) \\in [0, 1] \\times [0, 1], \\quad t > 0 \\\\\n",
    "u(x, y, 0) &= \\sin(\\pi x) \\sin(\\pi y), \\\\\n",
    "u &= 0 \\quad \\text{on } \\partial \\Omega,\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "with \\( \\kappa = 1 \\). The analytical solution is:\n",
    "\\[ u(x, y, t) = e^{-2 \\pi^2 t} \\sin(\\pi x) \\sin(\\pi y) \\]\n",
    "The maximum temperature \\( u_{\\text{max}}(t) = e^{-2 \\pi^2 t} \\) (at \\( (x, y) = (0.5, 0.5) \\)) is compared at \\( t = 0.15 \\).\n",
    "\n",
    "**h-Refinement**: Mesh resolutions \\( nx \\times ny = 20\\times20, 40\\times40, 60\\times60, 100\\times100 \\).\n",
    "**p-Refinement**: Element types:\n",
    "- `nn3_tri`: Linear triangle (P1, 3 nodes).\n",
    "- `nn6_tri`: Quadratic triangle (P2, 6 nodes).\n",
    "- `nn4_quad`: Linear quadrilateral (Q1, 4 nodes).\n",
    "- `nn8_quad`: Quadratic quadrilateral (Q2, 8 nodes).\n",
    "\n",
    "The comparison includes a bar plot with error bars and a convergence plot of relative error vs. degrees of freedom."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib as mpl\n",
    "import pyvista\n",
    "import ufl\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from petsc4py import PETSc\n",
    "from mpi4py import MPI\n",
    "from dolfinx import fem, mesh, io, plot\n",
    "from dolfinx.fem.petsc import assemble_vector, assemble_matrix, create_vector, apply_lifting, set_bc\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define temporal parameters\n",
    "t = 0\n",
    "T = 0.15  # Stop at t = 0.15 since we only compare there\n",
    "num_steps = 150  # dt = 0.001 for better temporal accuracy\n",
    "dt = T / num_steps\n",
    "kappa = 1.0  # Diffusion coefficient\n",
    "t_compare = 0.15\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define mesh resolutions for h-refinement\n",
    "mesh_sizes = [(20, 20), (40, 40), (60, 60), (100, 100)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Define element types for p-refinement\n",
    "element_types = [\n",
    "    ('triangle', 'P', 1),  # nn3_tri: Linear triangle (P1)\n",
    "    ('triangle', 'P', 2),  # nn6_tri: Quadratic triangle (P2)\n",
    "    ('quadrilateral', 'Q', 1),  # nn4_quad: Linear quadrilateral (Q1)\n",
    "    ('quadrilateral', 'Q', 2)   # nn8_quad: Quadratic quadrilateral (Q2)\n",
    "]\n",
    "element_names = ['nn3_tri', 'nn6_tri', 'nn4_quad', 'nn8_quad']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The square domain is meshed with either triangular or quadrilateral elements, varying resolution and polynomial degree for h- and p-refinement."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create initial condition\n",
    "def initial_condition(x):\n",
    "    return np.sin(np.pi * x[0]) * np.sin(np.pi * x[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Analytical solution and maximum temperature\n",
    "def analytical_solution(x, t, kappa=1.0):\n",
    "    return np.exp(-2 * kappa * np.pi**2 * t) * np.sin(np.pi * x[0]) * np.sin(np.pi * x[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "def analytical_max_temperature(t, kappa=1.0):\n",
    "    return np.exp(-2 * kappa * np.pi**2 * t)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Time-Dependent Output\n",
    "Store the solution for the final refinement case for visualization in Paraview."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Store results for comparison\n",
    "results = {name: [] for name in element_names}\n",
    "dofs = {name: [] for name in element_names}  # Store degrees of freedom\n",
    "errors = {name: [] for name in element_names}  # Store relative errors\n",
    "analytical_u_max = analytical_max_temperature(t_compare, kappa)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Loop over mesh sizes and element types\n",
    "for nx, ny in mesh_sizes:\n",
    "    for idx, ((cell_type, family, degree), elem_name) in enumerate(zip(element_types, element_names)):\n",
    "        # Create mesh\n",
    "        cell_type_map = {'triangle': mesh.CellType.triangle, 'quadrilateral': mesh.CellType.quadrilateral}\n",
    "        domain = mesh.create_rectangle(\n",
    "            MPI.COMM_WORLD, [np.array([0, 0]), np.array([1, 1])], [nx, ny], cell_type_map[cell_type]\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create function space\n",
    "        V = fem.functionspace(domain, (family, degree))\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Store degrees of freedom\n",
    "        num_dofs = V.dofmap.index_map.size_global\n",
    "        dofs[elem_name].append(num_dofs)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create initial condition\n",
    "        u_n = fem.Function(V)\n",
    "        u_n.name = \"u_n\"\n",
    "        u_n.interpolate(initial_condition)\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Create boundary condition\n",
    "        fdim = domain.topology.dim - 1\n",
    "        boundary_facets = mesh.locate_entities_boundary(\n",
    "            domain, fdim, lambda x: np.full(x.shape[1], True, dtype=bool))\n",
    "        boundary_dofs = fem.locate_dofs_topological(V, fdim, boundary_facets)\n",
    "        bc = fem.dirichletbc(PETSc.ScalarType(0), boundary_dofs, V)\n",
    "        print(f'Mesh {nx}x{ny}, Element {elem_name}: Number of constrained DOFs = {len(boundary_dofs)}')\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Define variational problem\n",
    "        u, v = ufl.TrialFunction(V), ufl.TestFunction(V)\n",
    "        f = fem.Constant(domain, PETSc.ScalarType(0))\n",
    "        a = u * v * ufl.dx + kappa * dt * ufl.dot(ufl.grad(u), ufl.grad(v)) * ufl.dx\n",
    "        L = (u_n + dt * f) * v * ufl.dx\n",
    "        bilinear_form = fem.form(a)\n",
    "        linear_form = fem.form(L)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Assemble matrix and vector\n",
    "        A = assemble_matrix(bilinear_form, bcs=[bc])\n",
    "        A.assemble()\n",
    "        b = create_vector(linear_form)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Create solver\n",
    "        solver = PETSc.KSP().create(domain.comm)\n",
    "        solver.setOperators(A)\n",
    "        solver.setType(PETSc.KSP.Type.PREONLY)\n",
    "        solver.getPC().setType(PETSc.PC.Type.LU)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Define solution variable\n",
    "        uh = fem.Function(V)\n",
    "        uh.name = \"uh\"\n",
    "        uh.interpolate(initial_condition)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Time-dependent output for the last case\n",
    "        if nx == 100 and elem_name == 'nn8_quad':\n",
    "            xdmf = io.XDMFFile(domain.comm, f\"diffusion_2d_{elem_name}_{nx}x{ny}.xdmf\", \"w\")\n",
    "            xdmf.write_mesh(domain)\n",
    "            xdmf.write_function(uh, t)\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Time-stepping\n",
    "        t = 0\n",
    "        for i in range(num_steps):\n",
    "            t += dt\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Update right-hand side\n",
    "            with b.localForm() as loc_b:\n",
    "                loc_b.set(0)\n",
    "            assemble_vector(b, linear_form)\n",
    "            apply_lifting(b, [bilinear_form], [[bc]])\n",
    "            b.ghostUpdate(addv=PETSc.InsertMode.ADD_VALUES, mode=PETSc.ScatterMode.REVERSE)\n",
    "            set_bc(b, [bc])\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Solve\n",
    "            solver.solve(b, uh.x.petsc_vec)\n",
    "            uh.x.scatter_forward()\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Update previous solution\n",
    "            u_n.x.array[:] = uh.x.array\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Write to file for the last case\n",
    "            if nx == 100 and elem_name == 'nn8_quad':\n",
    "                xdmf.write_function(uh, t)\n",
    "\n",
    "            # Compute maximum temperature at t = 0.15\n",
    "            if abs(t - t_compare) < 1e-6:\n",
    "                u_max_num = np.max(uh.x.array)\n",
    "                results[elem_name].append(u_max_num)\n",
    "                relative_error = abs(u_max_num - analytical_u_max) / analytical_u_max\n",
    "                errors[elem_name].append(relative_error)\n",
    "                # Check boundary values\n",
    "                boundary_values = uh.x.array[boundary_dofs]\n",
    "                max_boundary_value = np.max(np.abs(boundary_values))\n",
    "                print(f'Mesh {nx}x{ny}, Element {elem_name}: Max absolute value on boundary at t={t:.3f} = {max_boundary_value:.2e}')\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Clean up\n",
    "        if nx == 100 and elem_name == 'nn8_quad':\n",
    "            xdmf.close()\n",
    "        solver.destroy()\n",
    "        b.destroy()\n",
    "        A.destroy()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualization with PyVista\n",
    "Create a GIF of the numerical solution for the last refinement case (\( 100\\times100 \), `nn8_quad`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualization for the last case (nx=100, nn8_quad)\n",
    "nx, ny = 100, 100\n",
    "domain = mesh.create_rectangle(\n",
    "    MPI.COMM_WORLD, [np.array([0, 0]), np.array([1, 1])], [nx, ny], mesh.CellType.quadrilateral\n",
    ")\n",
    "V = fem.functionspace(domain, ('Q', 2))\n",
    "uh = fem.Function(V)\n",
    "uh.name = \"uh\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Read the solution from the XDMF file\n",
    "xdmf = io.XDMFFile(domain.comm, f\"diffusion_2d_nn8_quad_{nx}x{ny}.xdmf\", \"r\")\n",
    "grid = pyvista.UnstructuredGrid(*plot.vtk_mesh(V))\n",
    "plotter = pyvista.Plotter()\n",
    "plotter.open_gif(\"u_time_2d_refined.gif\", fps=10)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(num_steps + 1):\n",
    "    t = i * dt\n",
    "    uh = xdmf.read_function(V, t)\n",
    "    grid.point_data[\"uh\"] = uh.x.array\n",
    "    warped = grid.warp_by_scalar(\"uh\", factor=1)\n",
    "    if i == 0:\n",
    "        viridis = mpl.colormaps.get_cmap(\"viridis\").resampled(25)\n",
    "        sargs = dict(title_font_size=25, label_font_size=20, fmt=\"%.2e\", color=\"black\",\n",
    "                     position_x=0.1, position_y=0.8, width=0.8, height=0.1)\n",
    "        renderer = plotter.add_mesh(warped, show_edges=True, lighting=False,\n",
    "                                    cmap=viridis, scalar_bar_args=sargs,\n",
    "                                    clim=[0, max(uh.x.array)])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        warped.points[:, :] = grid.warp_by_scalar(\"uh\", factor=1).points\n",
    "        warped.point_data[\"uh\"][:] = uh.x.array\n",
    "    plotter.write_frame()\n",
    "\n",
    "plotter.close()\n",
    "xdmf.close()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Comparison at t = 0.15\n",
    "Compare the maximum temperature at \\( t = 0.15 \\) across mesh resolutions and element types using a bar plot with error bars, and plot the convergence of relative error vs. degrees of freedom."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Bar plot with error bars\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "bar_width = 0.2\n",
    "mesh_labels = [f'{nx}x{ny}' for nx, ny in mesh_sizes]\n",
    "x = np.arange(len(mesh_sizes))\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, elem_name in enumerate(element_names):\n",
    "    ax.bar(x + i * bar_width, results[elem_name], bar_width, label=elem_name, capsize=5)\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.axhline(y=analytical_u_max, color='r', linestyle='--', label='Analytical')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Mesh Resolution (nx × ny)')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Maximum Temperature at t = 0.15')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Maximum Temperature Comparison: h- and p-Refinement at t = 0.15')\n",
    "ax.set_xticks(x + bar_width * (len(element_names) - 1) / 2)\n",
    "ax.set_xticklabels(mesh_labels)\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(True, which='both', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convergence plot: Relative error vs. DOFs\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "for elem_name in element_names:\n",
    "    ax.loglog(dofs[elem_name], errors[elem_name], 'o-', label=elem_name)\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('Degrees of Freedom')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('Relative Error in u_max at t = 0.15')\n",
    "ax.set_title('Convergence of Relative Error')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(True, which='both', linestyle='--', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print relative errors\n",
    "for elem_name in element_names:\n",
    "    for i, (nx, ny) in enumerate(mesh_sizes):\n",
    "        u_max_num = results[elem_name][i]\n",
    "        relative_error = errors[elem_name][i]\n",
    "        print(f'Element: {elem_name}, Mesh: {nx}x{ny}, u_max: {u_max_num:.6f}, Relative Error: {relative_error:.2e}')"
   ]
  },
  {
